{
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, predicting DDI solely based on drug molecular diagram structures may lead to insufficient accuracy.",
    "There are also innovative methods that utilize multimodal data or drug interaction information for prediction, yielding superior results, DPSP [23] predicts DDIs using a multimodal framework through drug substructure information as well as mono side effects, target proteins, enzymes, and pathways.",
    "NNPS [24] Predicts polypharmacy side effects by using novel feature vectors based on mono side effects, and drug-protein interaction information.Overall, numerous models have been developed for the prediction of DDI, demonstrating promising performance.",
    "Nonetheless, deep learning-based DDI prediction methods often fail to adequately address at least three prominent issues.",
    "Firstly, relying solely on drug molecular graph structures or sequence features provides limited drug embedding information, restricting the DDI prediction performance."
  ]
}